  "text": "5 out of the 51 significantly changed A. oryzae secretory components were identified through blast search based on the yeast secretory machinery components [CITATION_1] and have never been identified in A. oryzae from other studies. These novel A. oryzae secretory components are homologs to yeast ERD2 (AO090102000650), YOS9 (AO090023000334), JEM1 (AO090020000010), MNS1 (AO090003000057) and GAB1 (AO090023000750) all of which showed significant up-regulation in response to α-amylase overproduction.",
